        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"color:#0d0d0d\">During a genetics seminar, a professor challenges the postgraduate students with a fundamental question about the structure of genetic code. She asks, &quot;A codon, which is essential for the translation process in protein synthesis, consists of 2 consecutive nuclotides. Is this statement true or false?&quot;</span></span></span></span></span></p>",
