          "id": 37618,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">4</span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">If there are 4 consecutive nucleotides code for an amino acid. Then how many amino acid can be coded by nucleic acid?</span></span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q1423295",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 30442,
